<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-08-05T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-08-05T06:00:00-05:00" n="627" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d627">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">852.6363/984: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hayes</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-08-05T13:00:00+02:00">August 5,
                                    1943—1 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 2:31 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>2035. Your 1411, June 26, 3 p.m., paragraph 5. I am including landing
                            rights for American airlines in Spain as one of conditions for
                            furnishing aviation gas. British Ambassador requests permission for
                            British airlines be included. I assume there is no objection. Please
                            advise.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hayes</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>